ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: ANK (DINESH THAKURS ANK) Ank is a regularly performing Hindi Theatre group in Mumbai and has completed 40 years of regular theatre activity in Hindi with 82 quality plays and more than 7000 successful shows all over the country as well as overseas, making it one of the largest performing teams in Hindi in the country. Ank was created by Dinesh Thakur who had himself notched up nearly five decades of experience in Theatre. Theatre for Ank is not only entertainment, but a source of respite as well as rejuvenation to the audience and the performer; a custodian of values as well as a statement of cultural individuality in society. Having come into being in 1976 and picked up momentum in 1978 with the emergence of Prithvi theatre in Mumbai, Ank today has one of the largest bodies of work in Hindi participating in numerous festivals and having travelled extensively in India and abroad with its productions. Starting with almost non-existent Hindi theatre audiences in Mumbai, Ank took upon itself the task of not only creating a regular Hindi theatre-going and ticket buying audience but also of laying the foundations and holding together a group of committed and dedicated theatre workers. Today, Anks repetoire has run the entire gamut from original works in Hindi to the best in national and international theatre, from the thought-provoking and the serious to the tragical, from court-room dramas and the hilarious to the deeply comical and outright farcical. It was Anks `Hai Mera Dil which gave Prithvi theatre its first housefull and has now become the longest running comedy in the history of Hindi theatre with 1125 shows. Plays like Vijay Tendulkars `Anji(760 shows), `Khamosh! Adalat Jari Hai, and `Jaat Hi Poocho Sadhu Ki, Mohan Rakeshs `Aadhe Adhoore, Mahesh Elkunchwars Atmakatha, adaptations like `Beewion Ka Madarsa(830 shows), `Bhaagam Bhaag(664 shows), `Tere Pyar Mein, `Tum kya Jano Preet and Javed Siddiquis `Hamesha are prominent among Anks repertoire. Ank first took the initiative of staging 25 continuous shows of its classic farce Jaane Na Doongi and then 30 continuous shows of Girish Karnads monumental classic `Tughlaq.It was Anks prerogative to honour and felicitate theatre persons from Gujarati, Marathi, English and Hindi, critics, benefactors as well as well-wishers as a gesture of goodwill. Recognizing the great contribution of playwrights, Ank in its 24th year felicitated Vijay Tendulkar as the playwright of the millenium and performed 6 of his plays through the year. Our Founder president and Director Shri Dinesh Thakur was awarded The Sangeet Natak Akademi Award for Direction for 2009. Dineshji is also the recipient of the Rajasthan State Sangeet Natak Akademi Award. He was also awarded the V.Shantaram Lalit Kala Hindi Vishisht Sewa Award by the Maharashtra State Hindi Sahitya Akademy for his contribution in Theatre. Ank is also probably the only theatre group to have donned the mantle of cultural ambassadors when invited by the Government of Mauritius to perform during our Republic day celebrations in that country.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Ankur Pratishthan is working in the fields of agriculture, education, women empowerment microfinance, water management, etc. In agriculture it is working to promote organic farming in 20 villages in Ambajogai tahsil. We have so far contacted 3000 farmers and many are following the procedure of organic farming. Various demonstration and presentations have been arranged over past few years on Ankur Pratishthan farm as well as in the farms of farmers about the preparation of fertilizers and pesticides based on organic farming. Organic produce is marketed in the weekly Bazaar started by Ankur Pratishthan. As the certification of organic farming individually is very costly so the method of PGS through group certification is followed. Ankur Pratishthan is situated at 10 kilometers away from Ambajogai items like in the vermin compost and Vermin wash is prepared and demonstrated. Marathwada and particularly Beed district is an area is a rain shadowed region hence the water level here are very low this area is also drought vulnerable is nearly after every few years. The drinking water is provided by the government on this background we form to be working in these villages. In water resources we have to chosen two villages known as kodri and umrai for watershed the total development plan for water development are these two villages are is prepared and being submitted to NABARD. Water management workshops are held in many villages where the use of drip irrigation, sprinklers is promoted within farmers who have been affiliated to Ankur Pratishthan. The river two villages need to be dipping and widened so that the water from the rain and hens the level of water increases. The same work is being done in the next two months with the help of anther VO and local farmer. The project of identifying and promoting the rare, traditional straight variety seeds from the local area is being implemented in twenty villages in two tahshils Ambajogai and Kaij . ten farmer each villages are chosen for giving corresponding seed and multiplying . From last six years the self help gropes of farm women are farmed in this twenty villages .the no. is eighty two. Many of them are linked to the banks , same are managed by us only. As per micro finance method the finance is given to them for some small business. The sample business finance are dairy ,saree shops , milk products consumer shop etc. regular meetings of these SHGs are held ,the vocational training programs are also held . Education- one primary English medium school is being run by us in Ambajogai town. Various activities such as gathering, competition, parents meeting etc. are held regularly. The school from the villages co contacted regularly and awareness in environment, tree plantation, seed identification , is done among to students.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Centre for Enquiry into Health and Allied Themes (CEHAT) is the research centre of Anusandhan Trust, conducting research, action, service and advocacy on health and related issues. CEHATs objectives are to undertake socially relevant research and advocacy projects on various socio-political aspects of health, establish direct services and programmes to demonstrate how health services can be made accessible equitably and ethically; disseminate information through databases and relevant publications, supported by a well stocked and specialized library and a documentation centre. CEHATs projects are based on its ideological commitments and priorities, and are focused on four broad themes, 1.Health services and Financing, 2.Health Legislation and Patients Rights, 3. Women and Health, 4.Investigation and Treatment of Psycho-Social Trauma. CEHAT recognises Violence Against Women as a public health and human rights issue and has been working on the subject since 1998. It has engaged with the health systems and professionals on the issue by setting up models that are gender sensitive and that provide comprehensive health care services for survivors of domestic violence and sexual assault. These services include psychosocial support, documentation of violence, legal services and follow up medical care. Training and capacity building of health care providers is the cornerstone of these interventions and this is ongoing. Services have been set up and staff of hospital has been trained to provide these services.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: The proposer Agency - Swargiya Haribhau Kulkarni Vishwast Manch (SHK Trust) is registered after the great personality , Shri Haribhau Kulkarni (1930-1989) had dedicated his whole life to the art and science of running public libraries and spread of the Culture of Reading. He is still remembered for his vision, social experiments and extraordinary demonstrative work done at Srirampur Public Library, Tq. Srirampur, District Ahmadnagar of Maharashtra State. His memories are still preserved in the form of the Municipal hall named after him and the public library now converted into E-Library inaugurated at the hands of Bharat Ratna and Ex-President of India Shri APJ Abdul Kalam at Srirampur in 2014. First fifteen years of the Trust was of silent working specially for downtrodden children at schools in Sangali district. A new office at Prachi, Atreya Society, Gokhale Nagar, Pune -16 was established in 2015 for activities of Astron. The activities of the Trust expanded geographically and volumetrically after 2004. Achievements of the proposer agency: Within last three years, after establishment of new department named Astron, the achievements of the proposer agency in the direction of realization the dream portal are as follows: a)Internal team building of passionate amateur astronomers and youngsters b)Conduct of Astronomy related outreach programs for various target groups with different age groups and variety background c)Creating In-house audio visual production expertise d)Networking of enthusiasts to work for spread of Astronomy knowledge e)Visiting and studying online education portals to know their functioning - academic, professional and technical aspect f)Establishing contacts with the stalwarts in the field of Astronomy and science as well as in the social field to get inspiration, vision and guidance g)Production of low cost dummy and pilot short films, audio visual teasers and presentations in the field of Astronomy and social messages h)Networking of likeminded individuals and institutions i)Creation of own website which is in the process of converting into the portal Much is still to be done to fulfill the proposer agencys passion of creating a dedicated and unique educational portal for online Astronomy education and look forward to NCSTC for support in this regard. The highlights of the work done by the proposer agency are as follows: 1.Astrotainment is an annual signature program of Astron-SHK Trust entering into the third year of success. The motto of Astrotainment is Approaching Astronomy through Entertainment which is getting an astonishing response of the age groups ranging from 12 to 84 years. 2.Astron also collaborated with University of Lancashire(U.K.), GMRT, IUCCA, NCL Innovation Park, Aakash-Mitra, Navnirmitee, Municipal Science Park and many others for various events related to Astronomy. 6.Production of a character film of a personality dedicated to administration for quality higher education and four social advt films (2014-2016) 7.Astron, a new Department was set up in 2011 which started extension activities relating to Astronomy. The growth of Astron activities and spread proved its quality. Thanks to the young brigade associated with Astron.
